@Issac Steele

lol, glorious

No, not exactly.

The signal is coming from a very distant point in space. It can be received by any sufficiently powerful radio receiver that happens to listen in. That's not good.

So the containment procedure is to send a space probe in that direction and have the probe transmit a masking signal back to Earth, so no one but the Foundation can access the original signal and anyone who stumbles upon it thinks it's just the probe doing its thing.





